y. I wonder, how people can really congratulate themselves on obtaining a piece of gear that they really didn't have to work for.<br><br>Sure, in the whole sense of killing Mob A for the elusive last piece can be considered working, but I have a problem with the fact that there's no competition for it. You know when it will come up, you know when you will have your chance, you know when you will get your epic. How terribly boring, especially if you happen to be at the end of a very... very long list.<br><br>Is it really okay to just say, 'Hey, let's just hand out epics and such to those who have no drive to scout a mob, to time a mob, to gather faster than others in the sake of competition, because they just want their epic' ? Seems to take a lot of the fun of EQ out of it..<br><br> <p><br><br><hr><p align="center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/slytlidisturbed/images/meadvae.jpg"></a><br><small><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60323">Sage Vaeluudaar Asha`man, Sorceror</a><b> :: </b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=301029 ">Meaduudar Malevolent, ShadowKnight</a><br><a href="http://www.furys-edge.com">the edge of teh fury~</a><b> :: </b><a href="http://www.meadbh.net/LoDaB/">no, you still can't join!</a></small></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uclaudshadowflare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/4/02 7:44:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1354.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.the-commune.com/forum/images/avatars/40.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Annoying ass rotations..</span><hr size=1> I think forming a strategy and having to wa