ation, it is impossible.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxisrene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xisrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/4/02 11:01:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1354.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Annoying ass rotations..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>Do you honestly believe that uberguild_01 would be like: Woot! VS is up, everyone leave VT and get to KC asap!<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Ummm...<br><br>1.  It doesn't matter how fucking Uber the guild is, they still need to gank VS to get epics for their twink wizards.<br><br>2. If the guild is in VT, they don't need &quot;everyone&quot;. All they need is one wizard with manaburn.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>Yes, occasionaly a larger guild would outmobilise a smaller, but hey, thats tough luck. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>But hey, I don't remember reading on my EverQuest box &quot;Get into pissing matches with other players regularly! Great fun for all!&quot;<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>If anything it would just teach those smaller guilds to mobilise quicker, which I'm sure most guild leaders would see as a blessing. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Yes, it's all about those smaller guilds learning how to outmobilize guilds that are 2-3 times larger and do nothing but raid (thus, by logging on their members are by definition ready to mobilize and kill something).<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>Yes it woul